# Cypress Standards

Use these standards for any Cypress-related code or guidance in this repository.

- Prefer behavior-focused E2E tests that validate what users see and do.
- Keep tests independent, deterministic, and CI-safe.
- Use stable selectors (`data-cy` preferred); avoid style or DOM-structure selectors.
- Do not use arbitrary time waits (for example `cy.wait(5000)`).
- Use `cy.intercept()` aliases for critical network behavior and assertions.
- Keep tests short and focused; split multi-workflow coverage into separate specs.
- Use page objects for reusable interactions and shared selectors.
- Use fixtures for deterministic test data and avoid hardcoded sensitive values.
- Follow naming convention `*.cy.ts` for Cypress spec files.

For detailed project guidance:

- Use `AGENTS.md` for general engineering and change-management standards.
- Use `AGENT-CYRPRESS.md` for Cypress-specific standards and generation workflow.
